    "review": [
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "Christine Clickner"
            },
            "reviewBody": "Just made for the first time. I did substitute 1 C \n\nfrozen blueberries for the pineapple. And, rather \n\nthan coconut oil I used 1 T of almond butter..\n\n2 handfuls of spinach leaves...everything else I \n\nleft the same. I made this using a Nutribullet high \n\nPower blender...oh, I added 2 dates. Very tasty!\n\nReminds me of a sweet tart candy!"
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "Louise"
            },
            "reviewBody": "I make a similar smoothie with green apple, banana, pineapple, frozen strawberries and peaches, kale and/or spinach and orange juice. The vitamin C in the orange juice helps absorb the iron in the kale and spinach, which is good if you're iron deficient like me."
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
                "@type": "Person",
                "name": "madison"
            },
            "reviewBody": "This smoothie is fantastic! Today is my first day of the green smoothie challenge, and I have to admit I was a bit skeptical about using spinach in a smoothie. You can't taste it at all!"
        },
        {
            "@type": "Review",
            "author": {
